description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time and part time posts available: To be considered please clearly state in your application if you want to be considered for 37.5 hours per week or 15 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated individual to join the Horton General Hospital’s Housekeeping team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Housekeepers are responsible for providing and maintaining a high standard of cleanliness. As a housekeeper you will work as part of the team to provide a clean safe environment for patients, staff and visitors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are assigned to a ward, you will also be supporting the nursing team with the delivery of patient food and beverages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will :-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have experience working in a highly pressured cleaning environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;be a confident communicator, dealing with various staff groups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;be able to manage their own workload, with the ability to work autonomously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have a desire to work in a healthcare environment, making our hospital clean and safe&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;live within 30 minutes travelling time to the hospital site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of cleaning in a healthcare environment and/or a food safety certificate will be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work, we will offer you:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a competitive salary and additional pay for any unsocial hours that you work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;access to a number of local and national discounts - on holidays, insurance, shopping and a whole lot more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;an industry leading pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;an environment where you expect to be supported and developed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you have read the job description and personal specification, as all applications will be scored against the required criteria.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 18th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planned interview date: tbc&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leeann Grant, Housekeeping Manager Leeann.Grant@ouh.nhs.uk 01295 227275 Monday - Friday between the hours of 1.00 pm - 3.00 pm&lt;/p&gt;
